issue.body:
### Terraform Core Version

1.5.5

### AWS Provider Version

5.23.0

### Affected Resource(s)

* aws_lambda_function

### Expected Behavior

Created lambda function. worked under 5.22.0

### Actual Behavior

got error 

```
Error: setting vpc_config: Invalid address to set: []string{"vpc_config", "0", "ipv6_allowed_for_dual_stack"}
```

### Relevant Error/Panic Output Snippet

_No response_

### Terraform Configuration Files

```
resource "aws_lambda_function" "lambda" {
  function_name = var.function_name
  description   = var.description
  role          = aws_iam_role.lambda.arn
  image_uri     = var.image_uri
  timeout       = var.timeout
  memory_size   = var.memory_size
  package_type  = var.package_type
  tags          = merge(var.tags, local.tags, { Custodian_Lambda_Error_Exclude = "YES PLEASE" })
  environment {
    variables = merge(var.environment_variables, {
      CLOUDWATCH_LOG_GROUP_NAME = aws_cloudwatch_log_group.lambda.name
      ENVIRONMENT               = var.environment
      REGION                    = var.region
    })
  }

  vpc_config {
    subnet_ids                  = var.subnet_ids
    security_group_ids          = var.security_group_ids
  }
}
```

### Steps to Reproduce

Ran the terraform code using AWS provider 5.22.0. It runs fine.
Under AWS provider 5.23.0 I get the error. 

Reverting back to 5.22.0 resolves the issue

### Terraform Core Version

v1.6.2

### AWS Provider Version

5.23.0

### Affected Resource(s)

 **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"** 

### Expected Behavior

I call **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"**  should not fail

### Actual Behavior


I call **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"** but get an error back:
_│ Error: reading Glue Catalog Table (<account no>:quality_dyko_src:image_metadata) partition indexes: EntityNotFoundException: Table image_metadata not found.
│ {
│   RespMetadata: {
│     StatusCode: 400,
│     RequestID: "ded00c84-ef74-4b32-93d0-5b0592d70eeb"
│   },
│   Message_: "Table image_metadata not found."
│ }_

If I look at the logs I see the error happens on **GetPartitionIndexes**
It seems it sends the structure

Sending the Account no in the --catalog-id gives the error:

> aws glue get-partition-indexes --catalog-id 964290010106 --database-name quality_dyko_pre --table-name image_metadata

}

issue.body:
### Terraform Core Version

v1.6.2

### AWS Provider Version

5.23.0

### Affected Resource(s)

 **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"** 

### Expected Behavior

I call **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"**  should not fail

### Actual Behavior


I call **resource "aws_glue_catalog_table"** but get an error back:
_│ Error: reading Glue Catalog Table (<account no>:quality_dyko_src:image_metadata) partition indexes: EntityNotFoundException: Table image_metadata not found.
│ {
│   RespMetadata: {
│     StatusCode: 400,
│     RequestID: "ded00c84-ef74-4b32-93d0-5b0592d70eeb"
│   },
│   Message_: "Table image_metadata not found."
│ }_

If I look at the logs I see the error happens on **GetPartitionIndexes**
It seems it sends the structure 
2023-10-27T10:08:28.946+0200 [DEBUG] provider.terraform-provider-aws_v5.23.0_x5.exe: HTTP Request Sent: http.request.header.authorization="AWS4-HMAC-SHA256 Credential=ASIA************32GU/20231027/eu-west-1/glue/aws4_request, SignedHeaders=content-length;content-type;host;x-amz-date;x-amz-security-token;x-amz-target, Signature=*****" http.request_content_length=97 rpc.service=Glue tf_provider_addr=registry.terraform.io/hashicorp/aws tf_rpc=ReadResource @caller=github.com/hashicorp/aws-sdk-go-base/v2/awsv1shim/v2@v2.0.0-beta.38/logger.go:109 rpc.method=GetPartitionIndexes rpc.system=aws-api tf_resource_type=aws_glue_catalog_table aws.region=eu-west-1 http.method=POST http.user_agent="APN/1.0 HashiCorp/1.0 Terraform/1.6.2 (+https://www.terraform.io) terraform-provider-aws/5.23.0 (+https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws) aws-sdk-go/1.46.3 (go1.20.10; windows; 386)" net.peer.name=glue.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com http.url=https://glue.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/ tf_mux_provider="*schema.GRPCProviderServer" @module=aws http.flavor=1.1 http.request.header.x_amz_target=AWSGlue.GetPartitionIndexes tf_req_id=c741619f-877e-d8d3-d0a3-907c2bb7b891 http.request.header.content_type=application/x-amz-json-1.1 http.request.header.x_amz_security_token="*****"
  http.request.body=
  | **{"CatalogId":"<AccountNo>","DatabaseName":"quality_dyko_pre","TableName":"image_metadata"}**
   http.request.header.x_amz_date=20231027T080828Z tf_aws.sdk=aws-sdk-go timestamp="2023-10-27T10:08:28.946+0200"

The problem is that the **CatalogId** that is send is the **account number** and not the **CatalogId** of the **table**.

I can replicate the issue by using the aws cli:
Sending the Account no in the --catalog-id gives the error:
>  aws glue get-partition-indexes --catalog-id <AccountNo> --database-name quality_dyko_pre --table-name image_metadata      

An error occurred (EntityNotFoundException) when calling the GetPartitionIndexes operation: Table image_metadata not found.

Sending the CatalogID on the table  in the --catalog-id gives the correct answer:
> aws glue get-partition-indexes --catalog-id 964290010106 --database-name quality_dyko_pre --table-name image_metadata       
{
    "PartitionIndexDescriptorList": []
}

### Terraform Core Version

1.5.5

### AWS Provider Version

5.23.0

### Affected Resource(s)

* aws_lambda_function

### Expected Behavior

Created lambda function. worked under 5.22.0

### Actual Behavior

got error 

```
Error: setting vpc_config: Invalid address to set: []string{"vpc_config", "0", "ipv6_allowed_for_dual_stack"}
```

### Relevant Error/Panic Output Snippet

_No response_

### Terraform Configuration Files

```
resource "aws_lambda_function" "lambda" {
  function_name = var.function_name
  description   = var.description
  role          = aws_iam_role.lambda.arn
  image_uri     = var.image_uri

    variables = merge(var.environment_variables, {
      CLOUDWATCH_LOG_GROUP_NAME = aws_cloudwatch_log_group.lambda.name
      ENVIRONMENT               = var.environment
      REGION                    = var.region
    })
  }

  vpc_config {
    subnet_ids                  = var.subnet_ids
    security_group_ids          = var.security_group_ids
  }
}
```

### Steps to Reproduce

Ran the terraform code using AWS provider 5.22.0. It runs fine.
Under AWS provider 5.23.0 I get the error.

### Terraform Core Version

1.5.5

### AWS Provider Version

5.23.0

### Affected Resource(s)

* aws_lambda_function

### Expected Behavior

Created lambda function. worked under 5.22.0

### Actual Behavior

got error 

```
Error: setting vpc_config: Invalid address to set: []string{"vpc_config", "0", "ipv6_allowed_for_dual_stack"}
```

### Relevant Error/Panic Output Snippet

_No response_

### Terraform Configuration Files

```
resource "aws_lambda_function" "lambda" {
  function_name = var.function_name
  description   = var.description
  role          = aws_iam_role.lambda.arn
  image_uri     = var.image_uri
  timeout       = var.timeout
  memory_size   = var.memory_size
  package_type  = var.package_type
  tags          = merge(var.tags, local.tags, { Custodian_Lambda_Error_Exclude = "YES PLEASE" })
  environment {
    variables = merge(var.environment_variables, {
      CLOUDWATCH_LOG_GROUP_NAME = aws_cloudwatch_log_group.lambda.name
      ENVIRONMENT               = var.environment
      REGION                    = var.region
    })
  }

  vpc_config {
    subnet_ids                  = var.subnet_ids
    security_group_ids          = var.security_group_ids
  }
}
```

### Steps to Reproduce

Ran the terraform code using AWS provider 5.22.0. It runs fine.
Under AWS provider 5.23.0 I get the error.
